TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(20,50,1);
$b1 = random(2,15,1);
$c1 = random(12,35,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
The domain of the function
\( \displaystyle f(x) = \frac { $a1 } {$b1 x - $c1} \)
is all real numbers \(x\) except for \(x\) where \(x\) equals
\{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = $c1/$b1;

ANS(num_cmp($ans));

